  "Acceptable Use Policy": "Acceptable Use Policy\n\nEffective Date: June 9, 2026\nLast Updated: June 9, 2026\n\n1. Purpose\n\nThis Acceptable Use Policy (\u201cAUP\u201d) governs the use of P-Drive and establishes rules intended to protect users, infrastructure, and the integrity of the platform.\n\nBy using P-Drive, you agree to comply with this Policy.\n\nThis Policy supplements the P-Drive Terms of Service and Privacy Policy.\n\n2. About P-Drive\n\nP-Drive is operated by:\n\nParallelogram Foundation\n\nAn independent software development initiative founded by:\n\nSarwar Altaf Dar\n\nBurhan Hamid Dar\n\nContact:\n\nparallelogram.devs@gmail.com\n\nCountry:\n\nIndia\n\n3. User Responsibility\n\nUsers are solely responsible for:\n\nContent uploaded\n\nContent shared\n\nContent distributed\n\nAccount activity\n\nCompliance with applicable laws\n\nP-Drive does not assume ownership of user content.\n\n4. Permitted Use\n\nYou may use P-Drive for lawful purposes including:\n\nPersonal storage\n\nBackup storage\n\nEducational content\n\nWork-related files\n\nPersonal documents\n\nCreative projects\n\nCollaboration\n\nLegal file sharing\n\nProvided such use complies with this Policy.\n\n5. Prohibited Activities\n\nUsers may not use P-Drive to:\n\nIllegal Activities\n\nViolate applicable laws\n\nFacilitate criminal conduct\n\nPromote unlawful activities\n\nCircumvent legal restrictions\n\nFraud and Deception\n\nIdentity theft\n\nFinancial fraud\n\nImpersonation\n\nForgery\n\nScam operations\n\nSecurity Abuse\n\nMalware distribution\n\nViruses\n\nWorms\n\nRansomware\n\nSpyware\n\nUnauthorized access attempts\n\nCredential theft\n\nNetwork Abuse\n\nDDoS attacks\n\nBotnet operations\n\nTraffic flooding\n\nService disruption\n\nIntellectual Property Violations\n\nCopyright infringement\n\nTrademark infringement\n\nUnauthorized distribution of protected content\n\nHarmful Conduct\n\nHarassment\n\nThreats\n\nExtortion\n\nStalking\n\nAbuse\n\n6. Prohibited Content\n\nUsers may not upload, store, distribute, or share content that:\n\nViolates Law\n\nIllegal materials\n\nCriminal evidence intended for unlawful use\n\nContent prohibited by applicable law\n\nContains Malicious Software\n\nMalware\n\nExploits\n\nViruses\n\nTrojan software\n\nHarmful code\n\nPromotes Harm\n\nTerrorism\n\nViolent extremism\n\nCriminal organizations\n\nHuman trafficking\n\nViolates Rights\n\nCopyrighted content without authorization\n\nConfidential information without permission\n\nPersonal information disclosed unlawfully\n\n7. Privacy-Oriented Design\n\nP-Drive is designed to support user privacy and encrypted storage.\n\nHowever:\n\nPrivacy protections do not exempt users from compliance with applicable laws.\n\nUsers remain responsible for the content they upload.\n\n8. Automated Usage\n\nUsers may not:\n\nAbuse APIs\n\nExcessively automate uploads\n\nCircumvent quotas\n\nGenerate artificial traffic\n\nAttempt to overload infrastructure\n\nReasonable automation may be permitted where authorized.\n\n9. Fair Usage\n\nP-Drive resources are shared among users.\n\nUsers may not:\n\nAbuse storage systems\n\nExploit technical loopholes\n\nCircumvent subscription limitations\n\nConsume resources in a manner that negatively impacts other users\n\nP-Drive reserves the right to apply reasonable usage controls.\n\n10. Account Security\n\nUsers must:\n\nMaintain password security\n\nProtect authentication credentials\n\nReport unauthorized access promptly\n\nMaintain accurate account information\n\nUsers may not:\n\nShare credentials\n\nSell accounts\n\nTransfer accounts without authorization\n\n11. Reporting Violations\n\nUsers may report suspected violations by contacting:\n\nparallelogram.devs@gmail.com\n\nReports should include:\n\nDescription of the issue\n\nRelevant details\n\nSupporting evidence when available\n\n12. Investigation Rights\n\nP-Drive reserves the right to investigate potential violations where reasonably necessary to:\n\nProtect infrastructure\n\nProtect users\n\nMaintain platform integrity\n\nComply with legal obligations\n\nInvestigations may include:\n\nAccount review\n\nActivity review\n\nMetadata analysis\n\nSecurity assessments\n\nP-Drive does not guarantee proactive monitoring of all user content.\n\n13. Enforcement\n\nViolations may result in:\n\nWarnings\n\nFeature restrictions\n\nTemporary suspension\n\nPermanent suspension\n\nAccount termination\n\nLegal action where appropriate\n\nEnforcement decisions may be made at P-Drive\u2019s reasonable discretion.\n\n14. No Guarantee of Monitoring\n\nP-Drive does not guarantee continuous monitoring of all content, activity, or communications.\n\nUsers remain solely responsible for their conduct and uploaded content.\n\n15. Changes to this Policy\n\nP-Drive may update this Acceptable Use Policy periodically.\n\nUpdated versions may be published through:\n\nThe application\n\nOfficial websites\n\nRelated services\n\nContinued use of P-Drive constitutes acceptance of revised versions.\n\n16. Contact Information\n\nP-Drive\n\nOperated by:\n\nParallelogram Foundation\n\nFounded by:\n\nSarwar Altaf Dar\n\nBurhan Hamid Dar\n\nEmail:\n\nparallelogram.devs@gmail.com\n\nCountry:\n\nIndia\n\n17. Final Statement\n\nP-Drive aims to provide a secure, privacy-focused, and reliable storage platform.\n\nUsers are expected to act responsibly, respect applicable laws, respect the rights of others, and use the service in good faith.\n\nFailure to do so may result in enforcement actions as described in this Policy.",
  "Data Retention Policy": "Data Retention Policy\n\nEffective Date: June 9, 2026\nLast Updated: June 9, 2026\n\n1. Purpose\n\nThis Data Retention Policy explains how P-Drive stores, retains, deletes, and manages user information, files, account records, logs, and related data.\n\nThe purpose of this policy is to promote transparency regarding how long information may remain within P-Drive systems.\n\n2. About P-Drive\n\nP-Drive is operated by:\n\nParallelogram Foundation\n\nAn independent software development initiative founded by:\n\nSarwar Altaf Dar\n\nBurhan Hamid Dar\n\nContact Email:\n\nparallelogram.devs@gmail.com\n\nCountry:\n\nIndia\n\n3. General Principles\n\nP-Drive aims to:\n\nMinimize unnecessary data retention\n\nProtect user privacy\n\nMaintain service reliability\n\nComply with legal obligations\n\nImprove security practices\n\nData is generally retained only for as long as reasonably necessary.\n\n4. Categories of Data\n\nP-Drive may process and retain the following categories of information:\n\nAccount Information\n\nExamples:\n\nName\n\nUsername\n\nEmail address\n\nProfile image\n\nAuthentication details\n\nAccount preferences\n\nUser Content\n\nExamples:\n\nUploaded files\n\nFolder information\n\nFile metadata\n\nStorage information\n\nOperational Data\n\nExamples:\n\nLogin records\n\nSession information\n\nDevice information\n\nError logs\n\nSecurity logs\n\nBilling Information\n\nExamples:\n\nSubscription status\n\nPurchase history\n\nTransaction identifiers\n\n5. User Files\n\nUploaded files may remain stored until:\n\nThe user deletes the file\n\nThe account is deleted\n\nStorage limitations require action\n\nLegal obligations require removal\n\nTechnical issues require corrective action\n\nP-Drive does not guarantee indefinite retention of uploaded content.\n\nUsers should maintain independent backups of important files.\n\n6. Deleted Files\n\nWhen a user deletes a file:\n\nThe file may not be immediately removed from all systems.\n\nDeletion may involve:\n\nPrimary storage removal\n\nBackup removal\n\nReplication cleanup\n\nCache expiration\n\nDeletion processing times may vary.\n\nCertain residual copies may temporarily remain within backup systems for operational purposes.\n\n7. Account Information Retention\n\nAccount information may be retained while:\n\nThe account remains active\n\nThe user continues using services\n\nSecurity obligations require retention\n\nLegal obligations require retention\n\nRetention periods may vary depending on operational requirements.\n\n8. Account Deletion\n\nUsers may request account deletion.\n\nFollowing deletion requests:\n\nAccount access may be disabled\n\nPersonal information may be scheduled for removal\n\nAssociated content may be scheduled for deletion\n\nCertain records may be retained where reasonably necessary for:\n\nLegal compliance\n\nSecurity investigations\n\nFraud prevention\n\nDispute resolution\n\n9. Metadata Retention\n\nP-Drive may retain limited metadata including:\n\nFile sizes\n\nUpload timestamps\n\nDownload timestamps\n\nStorage usage records\n\nOperational statistics\n\nMetadata may be retained longer than file contents when required for legitimate operational purposes.\n\n10. Security Logs\n\nSecurity-related logs may be retained to:\n\nDetect abuse\n\nInvestigate incidents\n\nImprove platform security\n\nProtect users\n\nMaintain service integrity\n\nRetention periods may vary depending on security requirements.\n\n11. Diagnostic and Error Logs\n\nDiagnostic information may be retained for:\n\nTroubleshooting\n\nPerformance analysis\n\nReliability improvements\n\nBug resolution\n\nSuch information may be periodically removed or anonymized.\n\n12. Subscription and Billing Records\n\nBilling records may be retained as reasonably necessary for:\n\nAccounting purposes\n\nFinancial audits\n\nTax compliance\n\nDispute resolution\n\nFraud prevention\n\nRetention periods may depend on applicable legal requirements.\n\n13. Backup Systems\n\nP-Drive may maintain backup systems designed to:\n\nImprove reliability\n\nRecover from failures\n\nProtect against accidental loss\n\nData contained within backup systems may remain available for limited periods following deletion from primary systems.\n\nBackup removal may occur according to operational schedules.\n\n14. Legal Retention Requirements\n\nCertain information may be retained longer when required by:\n\nApplicable law\n\nCourt orders\n\nRegulatory obligations\n\nLawful governmental requests\n\nSuch retention may continue beyond ordinary deletion schedules.\n\n15. Data Anonymization\n\nWhere appropriate, P-Drive may:\n\nAnonymize information\n\nAggregate information\n\nRemove identifying elements\n\nAnonymized data may be retained for research, analytics, security, or operational purposes.\n\n16. User Responsibility\n\nUsers are responsible for:\n\nMaintaining backups\n\nDownloading important files before deletion\n\nVerifying account information\n\nManaging stored content\n\nP-Drive is not responsible for losses resulting from user-initiated deletion actions.\n\n17. Data Destruction Practices\n\nWhen data is scheduled for removal, P-Drive may utilize reasonable technical measures intended to:\n\nRemove active records\n\nEliminate unnecessary copies\n\nReduce residual retention\n\nProtect deleted information from unauthorized access\n\nComplete removal across all systems may not occur instantly.\n\n18. Retention Limitations\n\nBecause of:\n\nDistributed systems\n\nReplication mechanisms\n\nBackup processes\n\nTechnical constraints\n\ncertain information may temporarily persist beyond deletion requests.\n\nP-Drive seeks to minimize such retention where reasonably possible.\n\n19. Policy Changes\n\nP-Drive may update this Data Retention Policy periodically.\n\nUpdated versions may be published through:\n\nThe application\n\nOfficial websites\n\nRelated services\n\nContinued use of P-Drive constitutes acceptance of updated versions.\n\n20. Contact Information\n\nP-Drive\n\nOperated by:\n\nParallelogram Foundation\n\nFounded by:\n\nSarwar Altaf Dar\n\nBurhan Hamid Dar\n\nEmail:\n\nparallelogram.devs@gmail.com\n\nCountry:\n\nIndia\n\n21. Final Statement\n\nP-Drive is committed to responsible data handling practices and privacy-conscious retention policies.\n\nWhile we strive to minimize retention wherever reasonably possible, certain operational, legal, security, and technical requirements may require information to be retained for limited periods beyond user actions.\n\nUsers should always maintain independent backups of important information and should not rely solely upon any single storage provider for long-term preservation of critical data.",
