websites, resources, or services.\n\nP-Drive does not control and is not responsible for:\n\nContent\n\nAvailability\n\nSecurity\n\nPrivacy practices\n\nof external resources.\n\nUsers access such resources at their own risk.\n\n19. Updates to this Disclaimer\n\nThis Disclaimer may be updated periodically.\n\nUpdated versions may be published through:\n\nThe P-Drive application\n\nOfficial websites\n\nRelated services\n\nContinued use of P-Drive after updates constitutes acceptance of revised versions.\n\n20. Contact Information\n\nP-Drive\n\nOperated by:\n\nParallelogram Foundation\n\nFounded by:\n\nSarwar Altaf Dar\n\nBurhan Hamid Dar\n\nEmail:\n\nparallelogram.devs@gmail.com\n\nCountry:\n\nIndia\n\n21. Final Statement\n\nP-Drive is committed to building a privacy-focused, reliable, and user-friendly storage platform.\n\nHowever, all technology carries inherent risks.\n\nUsers should exercise reasonable caution, maintain independent backups, protect account credentials, and understand that no online service can guarantee perfect security, permanent availability, or complete protection against every possible threat.",
  "Privacy Policy": "Privacy Policy\n\nEffective Date: June 9, 2026\nLast Updated: June 9, 2026\n\n1. Introduction\n\nWelcome to P-Drive.\n\nP-Drive is operated by Parallelogram Foundation, an independent software development initiative founded by Sarwar Altaf Dar and Burhan Hamid Dar.\n\nThis Privacy Policy explains how P-Drive collects, uses, stores, protects, and processes information when you use our services.\n\nBy using P-Drive, you agree to the practices described in this Privacy Policy.\n\n2. About P-Drive\n\nP-Drive is a cloud storage and file management platform designed to help users securely store, organize, synchronize, and access digital content.\n\nP-Drive is built with privacy and security as core principles.\n\n3. Minimum Age Requirement\n\nYou must be at least 13 years old to use P-Drive.\n\nIf you are under the age required by applicable law in your jurisdiction, you must have permission from a parent or legal guardian.\n\n4. Information We Collect\n\nAccount Information\n\nWhen creating an account, we may collect:\n\nName\n\nUsername\n\nEmail address\n\nProfile image\n\nAuthentication information\n\nAccount preferences\n\nDevice Information\n\nWe may collect:\n\nDevice model\n\nOperating system version\n\nApplication version\n\nLanguage preferences\n\nCrash diagnostics\n\nPerformance metrics\n\nUsage Information\n\nWe may collect:\n\nLogin activity\n\nFeature usage statistics\n\nStorage usage\n\nUpload and download activity\n\nSession information\n\n5. Files and Content\n\nP-Drive allows users to upload files and content.\n\nEncryption\n\nP-Drive is designed so that files may be encrypted before storage.\n\nWhere encryption is enabled:\n\nFile contents are encrypted prior to storage.\n\nP-Drive personnel are not intended to access file contents during normal operation.\n\nFile contents may not be readable without the appropriate decryption credentials.\n\nMetadata\n\nWhile file contents may be encrypted, certain metadata may still be processed, including:\n\nFile names\n\nFile sizes\n\nUpload timestamps\n\nDownload timestamps\n\nStorage usage statistics\n\n6. How We Use Information\n\nWe use collected information to:\n\nProvide the P-Drive service\n\nAuthenticate users\n\nMaintain account security\n\nImprove application performance\n\nPrevent abuse and fraud\n\nRespond to support requests\n\nDevelop new features\n\nComply with legal obligations\n\n7. Storage Infrastructure\n\nP-Drive may utilize a combination of storage providers, cloud services, third-party infrastructure, and internally managed systems.\n\nAs a result:\n\nData may be stored on multiple systems.\n\nData processing may occur through third-party service providers.\n\nReasonable safeguards are implemented to protect user information.\n\n8. Information Sharing\n\nP-Drive does not sell personal information.\n\nInformation may be shared only when necessary:\n\nService Providers\n\nThird-party providers assisting with:\n\nAuthentication\n\nStorage\n\nInfrastructure\n\nAnalytics\n\nSecurity\n\nLegal Requirements\n\nInformation may be disclosed if required by:\n\nCourt orders\n\nGovernment requests\n\nApplicable law\n\nProtection of legal rights\n\n9. Security\n\nP-Drive implements reasonable administrative, technical, and organizational measures designed to protect information.\n\nExamples include:\n\nEncryption technologies\n\nSecure authentication\n\nAccess controls\n\nMonitoring systems\n\nSecurity reviews\n\nHowever:\n\nNo method of transmission or storage is completely secure.\n\nP-Drive cannot guarantee absolute security.\n\n10. User Responsibilities\n\nUsers are responsible for:\n\nMaintaining password security\n\nProtecting recovery credentials\n\nProtecting encryption credentials\n\nKeeping devices secure\n\nMonitoring account activity\n\nLoss of encryption credentials may result in permanent loss of access to files.\n\n11. Data Retention\n\nP-Drive retains information only as long as reasonably necessary for:\n\nService operation\n\nLegal compliance\n\nSecurity purposes\n\nAccount maintenance\n\nRetention periods may vary depending on the type of information.\n\n12. Account Deletion\n\nUsers may request deletion of their account.\n\nUpon deletion:\n\nAccount information may be removed.\n\nAssociated content may be removed.\n\nCertain records may be retained where required by law, security obligations, or legitimate operational needs.\n\nDeletion may not be immediate.\n\n13. International Data Transfers\n\nInformation may be processed and stored in locations outside your country of residence.\n\nBy using P-Drive, you acknowledge that information may be transferred and processed in different jurisdictions.\n\n14. Third-Party Services\n\nP-Drive may integrate with third-party services.\n\nThese services maintain their own privacy policies.\n\nP-Drive is not responsible for the privacy practices of third-party services.\n\nUsers should review the policies of those providers separately.\n\n15. Children\u2019s Privacy\n\nP-Drive is not directed toward children under 13 years of age.\n\nIf we become aware that information has been collected from a child in violation of applicable laws, reasonable steps may be taken to remove such information.\n\n16. Changes to This Policy\n\nP-Drive may update this Privacy Policy from time to time.\n\nUpdated versions will be posted within the application, website, or related services.\n\nContinued use of P-Drive following updates constitutes acceptance of the revised policy.\n\n17. Contact Information\n\nFor questions regarding this Privacy Policy:\n\nP-Drive\nOperated by Parallelogram Foundation\n\nFounded by:\n\nSarwar Altaf Dar\n\nBurhan Hamid Dar\n\nEmail: parallelogram.devs@gmail.com\n\nCountry: India\n\n18. Disclaimer\n\nP-Drive is provided on an \u201cas available\u201d and \u201cas is\u201d basis.\n\nWhile P-Drive is designed with privacy and security considerations, no service can guarantee:\n\nAbsolute privacy\n\nAbsolute security\n\nUninterrupted availability\n\nPermanent accessibility of stored content\n\nUsers should maintain their own backups of important information.",
  "Refund & Subscription Policy": "Refund & Subscription Policy\n\nEffective Date: June 9, 2026\nLast Updated: June 9, 2026\n\n1. Introduction\n\nThis Refund & Subscription Policy governs all purchases, subscriptions, premium services, storage plans, and paid features offered through P-Drive.\n\nBy purchasing a subscription or paid service, you agree to this Policy.\n\n2. About P-Drive\n\nP-Drive is operated by:\n\nParallelogram Foundation\n\nAn independent software development initiative founded by:\n\nSarwar Altaf Dar\n\nBurhan Hamid Dar\n\nContact Email:\n\nparallelogram.devs@gmail.com\n\nCountry of Operation:\n\nIndia\n\n3. Subscription Services\n\nP-Drive may offer:\n\nMonthly subscriptions\n\nAnnual subscriptions\n\nPremium storage plans\n\nPromotional plans\n\nAdditional storage purchases\n\nFuture premium features\n\nAvailable plans and pricing may change over time.\n\n4. Billing\n\nWhen purchasing a subscription:\n\nCharges are billed according to the selected plan.\n\nPrices are displayed before purchase.\n\nApplicable taxes may be added where required by law.\n\nUsers are responsible for ensuring payment information remains valid.\n\n5. Automatic Renewals\n\nWhere supported:\n\nSubscriptions may automatically renew at the end of each billing cycle unless cancelled before renewal.\n\nUsers may manage subscription settings through the platform used for purchase.\n\nFailure to cancel before renewal may result in the next billing cycle being charged.\n\n6. Free Trials\n\nP-Drive may offer:\n\nFree trials\n\nPromotional access\n\nTemporary premium features\n\nUnless otherwise stated:\n\nPaid subscriptions begin automatically after the trial period ends.\n\nUsers remain responsible for managing trial cancellations.\n\n7. General Refund Policy\n\nDue to the nature of digital services and cloud storage, refunds are generally limited.\n\nStorage resources, infrastructure costs, and service provisioning may begin immediately after purchase.\n\nRefund requests are reviewed individually.\n\n8. Eligible Refund Situations\n\nRefund requests may be considered when:\n\nDuplicate payments occurred.\n\nBilling errors occurred.\n\nTechnical issues prevented activation of purchased services.\n\nUsers were charged incorrectly.\n\nPurchases were processed due to verified platform errors.\n\nApproval is not guaranteed.\n\n9. Non-Refundable Situations\n\nRefunds will generally not be provided for:\n\nChange of mind.\n\nLack of usage.\n\nFailure to cancel before renewal.\n\nUser error during purchase.\n\nStorage already consumed.\n\nAccount suspension caused by policy violations.\n\nViolations of Terms of Service.\n\nLoss of files resulting from user actions.\n\nDissatisfaction based solely on preference.\n\n10. Subscription Cancellation\n\nUsers may cancel subscriptions at any time.\n\nCancellation prevents future renewal charges.\n\nCancellation does not automatically generate a refund for current billing periods.\n\nUnless otherwise required by law:\n\nAccess to premium features may continue until the end of the active billing cycle.\n\n11. Chargebacks\n\nUsers are encouraged to contact P-Drive before initiating chargebacks.\n\nFraudulent or abusive chargebacks may result in:\n\nAccount restrictions\n\nService suspension\n\nTermination of access\n\nP-Drive reserves the right to dispute invalid chargeback claims.\n\n12. Payment Providers\n\nPayments may be processed through third-party providers.\n\nThese providers maintain independent policies regarding:\n\nPayments\n\nRefunds\n\nDisputes\n\nBilling\n\nUsers may also be subject to the policies of the payment provider used during purchase.\n\n13. Storage and Refunds\n\nStorage capacity may be allocated immediately after purchase.\n\nBecause storage resources may be provisioned instantly:\n\nRefund eligibility may be reduced once service delivery begins.\n\n14. Failed Payments\n\nIf a payment fails:\n\nP-Drive may:\n\nRetry billing\n\nRestrict premium features\n\nDowngrade account access\n\nSuspend premium services\n\nuntil payment issues are resolved.\n\n15. Promotional Plans\n\nPromotional offers, discounts, coupons, and special plans may be subject to additional conditions.\n\nCertain promotional purchases may be designated as non-refundable.\n\nSpecific promotional terms will be displayed when applicable.\n\n16. Account Termination and Refunds\n\nIf an account is terminated due to violations of:\n\nTerms of Service\n\nAcceptable Use Policy\n\nApplicable law\n\nusers may lose access to paid services.\n\nRefunds are generally not provided in such circumstances.\n\n17. Processing Time\n\nIf a refund is approved:\n\nProcessing times depend on:\n\nPayment provider\n\nBanking institution\n\nPayment method\n\nRefund completion may take several business days.\n\nP-Drive cannot guarantee specific banking timelines.\n\n18. Requesting a Refund\n\nTo request a refund, contact:\n\nparallelogram.devs@gmail.com\n\nInclude:\n\nRegistered email address\n\nTransaction details\n\nPurchase date\n\nReason for request\n\nSupporting information if available\n\nIncomplete requests may delay review.\n\n19. Policy Updates\n\nP-Drive may update this Refund Policy periodically.\n\nChanges become effective when published through:\n\nThe application\n\nOfficial websites\n\nRelated services\n\nContinued use of paid services constitutes acceptance of updated policies.\n\n20. Limitation of Liability\n\nTo the maximum extent permitted by law:\n\nP-Drive, Parallelogram Foundation, Sarwar Altaf Dar, Burhan Hamid Dar, contributors, contractors, and affiliates shall not be liable for:\n\nIndirect losses\n\nLost profits\n\nBusiness interruption\n\nConsequential damages\n\nData loss\n\nMissed renewal notices\n\nrelated to subscription services.\n\n21. Contact Information\n\nP-Drive\n\nOperated by:\n\nParallelogram Foundation\n\nFounded by:\n\nSarwar Altaf Dar\n\nBurhan Hamid Dar\n\nEmail:\n\nparallelogram.devs@gmail.com\n\nCountry:\n\nIndia\n\n22. Final Statement\n\nP-Drive strives to provide fair, transparent, and reliable subscription services.\n\nWhile we aim to resolve legitimate billing issues promptly, users are expected to review plan details carefully before making purchases and to manage subscriptions responsibly.",
  "Security Policy": "Security Policy\n\nEffective Date: June 9, 2026\nLast Updated: June 9, 2026\n\n1. Purpose\n\nThis Security Policy explains the security principles, practices, and responsibilities associated with the use of P-Drive.\n\nP-Drive is committed to protecting user accounts, stored information, infrastructure, and services through reasonable technical and organizational security measures.\n\n2. About P-Drive\n\nP-Drive is operated by:\n\nParallelogram Foundation\n\nAn independent software development initiative founded by:\n\nSarwar Altaf Dar\n\nBurhan Hamid Dar\n\nContact Email:\n\nparallelogram.devs@gmail.com\n\nCountry:\n\nIndia\n\n3. Security Philosophy\n\nP-Drive is designed around the following principles:\n\nPrivacy by design\n\nSecurity by design\n\nLeast privilege access\n\nData minimization\n\nSecure authentication\n\nEncryption-focused storage\n\nContinuous improvement\n\nSecurity is considered an ongoing process rather than a guarantee.\n\n4. Encryption\n\nP-Drive may utilize encryption technologies to protect information.\n\nWhere available:\n\nFile Encryption\n\nFiles may be encrypted before storage.\n\nThis design helps reduce unauthorized access to file contents.\n\nData Transmission\n\nInformation may be transmitted using encrypted communication protocols.\n\nCredential Protection\n\nAuthentication credentials may be protected using industry-standard security practices.\n\n5. Account Security\n\nUsers are responsible for:\n\nMaintaining strong passwords\n\nProtecting recovery credentials\n\nMaintaining device security\n\nProtecting authentication methods\n\nMonitoring account activity\n\nUsers should avoid:\n\nSharing passwords\n\nReusing passwords across services\n\nStoring credentials insecurely\n\n6. Infrastructure Security\n\nP-Drive may implement security controls including:\n\nAccess restrictions\n\nInfrastructure monitoring\n\nLogging systems\n\nAuthentication controls\n\nNetwork protections\n\nSecurity reviews\n\nSpecific technical implementations may change over time.\n\n7. Access Control\n\nAccess to operational systems is limited based on legitimate business and technical requirements.\n\nP-Drive seeks to apply the principle of least privilege whenever reasonably possible.\n\nAdministrative access may be restricted to authorized personnel only.\n\n8. Security Monitoring\n\nP-Drive may monitor systems for:\n\nService health\n\nAbuse detection\n\nSecurity threats\n\nOperational performance\n\nInfrastructure stability\n\nMonitoring may include logs, metadata, and operational diagnostics.\n\n9. User Responsibilities\n\nUsers are expected to:\n\nKeep software updated\n\nUse secure passwords\n\nEnable available security features\n\nProtect account credentials\n\nReport suspicious activity\n\nFailure to follow reasonable security practices may increase the risk of unauthorized access.\n\n10. Incident Response\n\nIn the event of a security incident, P-Drive may:\n\nInvestigate the incident\n\nContain affected systems\n\nImplement corrective measures\n\nRestore services\n\nNotify affected users when appropriate\n\nResponse actions may vary depending on the nature and severity of the incident.\n\n11. Security Limitations\n\nNo security system can provide absolute protection.\n\nUsers acknowledge that risks may include:\n\nSoftware vulnerabilities\n\nInfrastructure failures\n\nThird-party service disruptions\n\nHuman error\n\nCybersecurity threats\n\nUnauthorized access attempts\n\nP-Drive does not guarantee immunity from all security incidents.\n\n12. Third-Party Providers\n\nP-Drive may rely on third-party providers for:\n\nStorage infrastructure\n\nAuthentication services\n\nNetworking services\n\nSecurity tools\n\nCloud services\n\nSecurity of certain components may therefore depend partially on those providers.\n\nUsers may also be subject to the security practices of such providers.\n\n13. Vulnerability Reporting\n\nP-Drive welcomes responsible disclosure of security vulnerabilities.\n\nResearchers and users who discover a potential vulnerability should report it responsibly.\n\nReports may be sent to:\n\nparallelogram.devs@gmail.com\n\nPlease include:\n\nDescription of the issue\n\nReproduction steps\n\nSupporting information\n\nPotential impact\n\n14. Responsible Disclosure\n\nIndividuals reporting vulnerabilities are expected to:\n\nAct in good faith\n\nAvoid harming users\n\nAvoid accessing unauthorized data\n\nAvoid disrupting services\n\nAllow reasonable time for remediation\n\nP-Drive may investigate reported issues before taking action.\n\n15. Account Recovery\n\nUsers are responsible for maintaining recovery methods associated with their accounts.\n\nLoss of:\n\nPasswords\n\nRecovery information\n\nEncryption credentials\n\nmay result in loss of access to stored content.\n\nP-Drive may be unable to recover encrypted files in certain circumstances.\n\n16. Backup Responsibility\n\nAlthough P-Drive may implement storage redundancy and reliability measures, users remain responsible for maintaining independent backups of important data.\n\nUsers should not rely exclusively on a single storage provider for irreplaceable information.\n\n17. Availability and Security\n\nSecurity measures may occasionally require:\n\nMaintenance windows\n\nService interruptions\n\nFeature restrictions\n\nTemporary access limitations\n\nSuch actions may be taken to preserve platform security and reliability.\n\n18. Security Updates\n\nP-Drive may periodically update:\n\nSecurity controls\n\nAuthentication methods\n\nEncryption technologies\n\nInfrastructure protections\n\nwithout prior notice when necessary to protect users or services.\n\n19. Limitation of Liability\n\nTo the maximum extent permitted by law:\n\nP-Drive, Parallelogram Foundation, Sarwar Altaf Dar, Burhan Hamid Dar, contributors, contractors, and affiliates shall not be liable for damages resulting from:\n\nSecurity incidents\n\nData loss\n\nUnauthorized access\n\nThird-party attacks\n\nService disruptions\n\nInfrastructure failures\n\nUse of the service remains at the user\u2019s own risk.\n\n20. Policy Updates\n\nThis Security Policy may be updated periodically.\n\nUpdated versions may be published through:\n\nThe P-Drive application\n\nOfficial websites\n\nRelated services\n\nContinued use of P-Drive constitutes acceptance of revised versions.\n\n21. Contact Information\n\nP-Drive\n\nOperated by:\n\nParallelogram Foundation\n\nFounded by:\n\nSarwar Altaf Dar\n\nBurhan Hamid Dar\n\nEmail:\n\nparallelogram.devs@gmail.com\n\nCountry:\n\nIndia\n\n22. Final Statement\n\nP-Drive is committed to maintaining a privacy-focused and security-conscious platform.\n\nWhile we continuously work to improve security, users should understand that no technology, service, or infrastructure can guarantee complete protection against every possible threat.\n\nSecurity is a shared responsibility between P-Drive and its users.",
  "Terms of Service": "Terms of Service\n\nEffective Date: June 9, 2026\nLast Updated: June 9, 2026\n\n1. Acceptance of Terms\n\nWelcome to P-Drive.\n\nThese Terms of Service (\u201cTerms\u201d) govern your use of the P-Drive platform, applications, websites, services, and related technologies.\n\nBy accessing or using P-Drive, you agree to be bound by these Terms.\n\nIf you do not agree to these Terms, you must not use P-Drive.\n\n2. Service Operator\n\nP-Drive is operated by:\n\nParallelogram Foundation\n\nAn independent software development initiative founded by:\n\nSarwar Altaf Dar\n\nBurhan Hamid Dar\n\nSupport Contact:\n\nparallelogram.devs@gmail.com\n\nCountry of Operation:\n\nIndia\n\n3. Eligibility\n\nYou must be at least thirteen (13) years of age to use P-Drive.\n\nIf local laws require a higher age threshold, you must satisfy those requirements.\n\nBy using P-Drive, you represent that you meet the applicable age requirements.\n\n4. User Accounts\n\nYou are responsible for:\n\nMaintaining account security\n\nProtecting passwords\n\nProtecting recovery credentials\n\nMaintaining accurate account information\n\nAll activities occurring through your account\n\nYou agree not to:\n\nShare accounts\n\nSell accounts\n\nTransfer accounts without authorization\n\nCircumvent account restrictions\n\n5. Description of Service\n\nP-Drive provides:\n\nCloud storage services\n\nFile synchronization\n\nFile management\n\nFile organization\n\nSecure storage technologies\n\nSubscription-based storage plans\n\nFeatures may change over time.\n\nP-Drive may modify, suspend, or discontinue features at its discretion.\n\n6. Ownership of Content\n\nYou retain ownership of files and content uploaded to P-Drive.\n\nP-Drive does not claim ownership of your uploaded content.\n\nYou grant P-Drive only the limited rights necessary to:\n\nStore content\n\nProcess content\n\nTransfer content\n\nDeliver requested services\n\n7. User Responsibilities\n\nYou are solely responsible for:\n\nUploaded content\n\nShared content\n\nBackup practices\n\nCompliance with applicable laws\n\nP-Drive does not verify or monitor all uploaded content.\n\n8. Prohibited Activities\n\nYou agree not to use P-Drive for:\n\nIllegal activities\n\nFraud\n\nIdentity theft\n\nMalware distribution\n\nPhishing\n\nUnauthorized access attempts\n\nIntellectual property infringement\n\nSpam operations\n\nService abuse\n\nAutomated attacks\n\nYou may not:\n\nReverse engineer the service\n\nDisrupt infrastructure\n\nCircumvent security mechanisms\n\nAbuse APIs or network resources\n\n9. Privacy and Encryption\n\nP-Drive is designed with privacy-focused principles.\n\nWhere encryption is enabled:\n\nFiles may be encrypted before storage.\n\nFile contents may not be accessible during normal operation.\n\nHowever:\n\nP-Drive does not guarantee absolute privacy, absolute confidentiality, or immunity from all security risks.\n\nUsers remain responsible for protecting credentials and encryption keys.\n\n10. Storage Limits\n\nStorage allocations depend on the user\u2019s selected plan.\n\nP-Drive may:\n\nAdjust storage plans\n\nModify plan limits\n\nIntroduce new plans\n\nRetire existing plans\n\nReasonable notice may be provided when possible.\n\n11. Subscription Services\n\nCertain features may require a paid subscription.\n\nSubscriptions may include:\n\nMonthly plans\n\nAnnual plans\n\nPromotional plans\n\nPremium features\n\nSubscription details are displayed at the time of purchase.\n\n12. Payments\n\nUsers agree to pay applicable fees associated with selected services.\n\nPrices may change in the future.\n\nTaxes, fees, and applicable charges may apply depending on jurisdiction.\n\nFailure to pay may result in:\n\nService restrictions\n\nAccount limitations\n\nSuspension of premium features\n\n13. Refunds\n\nRefund eligibility is governed by the P-Drive Refund Policy.\n\nCertain purchases may be non-refundable where permitted by law.\n\n14. Account Suspension\n\nP-Drive may suspend or restrict accounts for:\n\nSecurity concerns\n\nFraud prevention\n\nAbuse prevention\n\nLegal compliance\n\nViolations of these Terms\n\nSuspension decisions may be temporary or permanent.\n\n15. Account Termination\n\nUsers may discontinue use of P-Drive at any time.\n\nP-Drive reserves the right to terminate accounts that:\n\nViolate these Terms\n\nEndanger infrastructure\n\nCreate legal risks\n\nAbuse platform resources\n\n16. Data Loss Disclaimer\n\nWhile P-Drive aims to provide reliable storage services, users acknowledge that:\n\nTechnical failures may occur.\n\nInfrastructure failures may occur.\n\nThird-party provider failures may occur.\n\nData corruption may occur.\n\nUsers are responsible for maintaining independent backups of important data.\n\nP-Drive does not guarantee permanent preservation of uploaded content.\n\n17. Service Availability\n\nP-Drive is provided on an \u201cas available\u201d basis.\n\nWe do not guarantee:\n\nContinuous uptime\n\nUninterrupted access\n\nError-free operation\n\nPermanent feature availability\n\nMaintenance periods and service interruptions may occur.\n\n18. Intellectual Property\n\nAll P-Drive software, branding, trademarks, designs, logos, interfaces, and related materials remain the property of P-Drive or its licensors.\n\nUsers may not copy, reproduce, distribute, or commercially exploit P-Drive intellectual property without authorization.\n\n19. Third-Party Services\n\nP-Drive may rely on third-party providers for:\n\nAuthentication\n\nStorage\n\nInfrastructure\n\nSecurity\n\nAnalytics\n\nAvailability of P-Drive may depend on such providers.\n\nP-Drive is not responsible for interruptions caused by third-party services.\n\n20. Limitation of Liability\n\nTo the maximum extent permitted by law:\n\nP-Drive, Parallelogram Foundation, Sarwar Altaf Dar, Burhan Hamid Dar, employees, contributors, contractors, and affiliates shall not be liable for:\n\nData loss\n\nBusiness interruption\n\nLost profits\n\nIndirect damages\n\nConsequential damages\n\nService outages\n\nThird-party actions\n\nUse of P-Drive is at your own risk.\n\n21. Indemnification\n\nYou agree to indemnify and hold harmless:\n\nP-Drive\n\nParallelogram Foundation\n\nSarwar Altaf Dar\n\nBurhan Hamid Dar\n\nfrom claims, liabilities, damages, costs, and expenses arising from:\n\nYour content\n\nYour actions\n\nViolations of these Terms\n\nViolations of applicable laws\n\n22. Changes to Terms\n\nP-Drive may modify these Terms periodically.\n\nUpdated versions may be posted through:\n\nThe application\n\nOfficial websites\n\nRelated services\n\nContinued use after updates constitutes acceptance of revised Terms.\n\n23. Governing Law\n\nThese Terms shall be governed by the laws of India.\n\nAny disputes arising under these Terms shall be subject to applicable courts and legal authorities within India.\n\n24. Severability\n\nIf any provision of these Terms is found invalid or unenforceable, the remaining provisions shall remain in effect.\n\n25. Contact Information\n\nP-Drive\n\nOperated by Parallelogram Foundation\n\nFounded by:\n\nSarwar Altaf Dar\n\nBurhan Hamid Dar\n\nEmail:\n\nparallelogram.devs@gmail.com\n\nCountry:\n\nIndia\n\n26. Entire Agreement\n\nThese Terms, together with the Privacy Policy and other applicable policies, constitute the entire agreement between the user and P-Drive regarding use of the service.",
